Next 12 does [support native ES modules](https://nextjs.org/blog/next-12#es-modules-support-and-url-imports) if the package has been correctly configured. (If not, it will fall back to CJS)

`react-graphql-syntax-highlighter` did not configure [its `package.json`](https://unpkg.com/browse/react-graphql-syntax-highlighter@0.0.2/package.json) correctly. It does not have a `type: "module"` nor `.mjs` extensions in it's `dist` folder.

See the requirements for ES Module detection in the Node.js documentation: https://nodejs.org/api/packages.html#determining-module-system

In addition, an `exports` field should be preferred over `main` as well:

https://nodejs.org/api/packages.html#package-entry-points

Please reach out to the author of the package, or if it's you, follow the steps from the Node.js documentation.



Adding the following to the `package.json`:

```js
  "type": "module",
  "exports": {
    ".": "./dist/index.js",
    "./style.css": "./dist/style.css"
  },
```

