I tried reproducing, but the stale-while-revalidate strategy works as expected:

```js
export default function Home(props) {
  return props.time
}

export function getStaticProps() {
  return {
    props: { time: new Date().toISOString() },
    revalidate: 5,
  }
}
```

The server correctly responds with the stale version on the first hit after the revalidation time, but the request after that will be the updated one since the cache has been updated in the background.

You can verify this by looking at the `x-nextjs-cache` response header.

